      "side": 1,
      "message": "At one point we talked about each flush call returning an ID and then having submit return an array of flushIDs to say which flushes were successfully submitted and possibly also which flushIDs failed to be submitted. Since we are decided to pass full ownership of the semaphores to the caller at flush time, is this something that is still needed? I could see some uses of it being nice, maybe.\n\nA complication to this is the currently flush calls that force a submit with them. If there are outstanding unsubmitted flushes how do we notify the client what go flushed during them. I guess we could add some outParam thing onto GrFlushInfo that matches whatever we decide to return from a normal submit call? Just need to make sure that can be ignored and all things still work who want the current behavior.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 433,
